    <text id="B1127T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>How lists the reports and forms he is sending to Richmond, presumably as a part
                    of the transfer from Staunton to Winchester.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau Refugees, Freedmen &amp; <abbr expan="Abandoned">A.</abbr> Lands
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr> O. Brown, <abbr
                            expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst Comr</abbr><lb/>Richmond <abbr
                            expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-10-06">October 6<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1865</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Colonel</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to transmit herewith my "Report of Civilians Employed", "Report
                    of Lands," "Account Current, Bureau Funds" with abstract of money received from
                    rents, abstract of Expenditures, 5 vouchers, and Return of Taxes witheld on
                    Salaries, a voucher to which will be forwarded as soon as the duplicate receipts
                    are received from the <abbr expan="Commissioner">Com<hi rend="super"
                    >r</hi></abbr> of <abbr expan="Internal">Int.</abbr> Revenue, "Return of <abbr
                        expan="Quartermaster">QM</abbr> Stores with Abstract <unclear>J</unclear>"
                    "account current <abbr expan="Quartermaster">Q.M.</abbr> Funds" with Abstract
                        <unclear>B</unclear> 1 voucher" all for the month of September 1865, with
                    Estimate of Funds for October 1865, I have no "Return of <unclear>C.C. &amp;
                        G.E.</unclear>" to make nor of "Bureau Property" or "Bureau C.C. &amp;
                    G.E."</p>

                <p>My "Report of Rations issued to Refugees, Freedmen &amp;c will be forwarded
                    with "Report of Schools", from Winchester, on or before the 10th <abbr
                        expan="instant">inst.</abbr></p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I am Colonel <lb/>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obed</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Servant">Servt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>W. Storer How<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> &amp; <abbr
                            expan="Assistant Quatermaster">AQM</abbr>, <abbr expan="Superintendent"
                            >Supt</abbr> Sixth District, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
